<li id="c243">
  <div class="cx" id="cx50280246">
   <h5> <a class="de">&nbsp;</a><span class="cu">Meteor Blades was for the Libya operation.</span>


<span class="crd ntb">(<a href="/comments/1211456/50280246#c243?mode=alone;showrate=1#c243">0+ / 0-</a>)</span>
  </h5>

  
  


  

  <div class="ct">
  
<p>Madeline Albright was for using military force to stop atrocities in Bosnia.<br />
Samantha Power was for both the Libya operation and was for using force to stop atrocities in Rwanda.<br />
Joe Biden was for pulling troops in Afghanistan but at the same time massively increasing drones strikes in the Afghan/Pakistan border region.<br />
President Obama was for using military force to take down OBL.<br />
President Clinton was for using military force to stop atrocities in Bosnia and restore a democratically elected leader in Haiti.</p>
<p>Speaking of Libya, the reason the intervention was launched was that Gadhafi was marching troops to Benghazi, vowing to exterminate the population.</p>
<p>The anti-war left opposed all of the above actions (or potential actions, in the case of Rwanda), but it's arguable as to whether refusing to use military force to stop an atrocity really is more moral than using military force to stop said atrocity. &nbsp;It's arguable as to whether using special forces to take down OBL really is an immoral act for use of military force. &nbsp;The anti-war left presumes that these are settled matters, that there's not a good faith argument to be made against their position.</p>
<p>At any rate, 100% pacifism has never been necessary to be "left", nor has it even been the case that being "anti-war" in particular instances is a characteristic of the left or characteristic of the moral high ground. &nbsp;For example, during the US Civil War, in the north it was <em>conservatives</em> who were "anti-war". &nbsp;During WWII, in the US it was <em>conservatives</em> (like Lindbergh) who were anti-war. &nbsp;But not only were those groups not "left" for their opposition to the respective wars, &nbsp;neither of those groups even held the moral high ground for being anti-war in those cases, quite the contrary in fact.</p>

  </div>
  <div class="cf">
  <p class="sig"></p>
  <p class="cb">by <a href="/user/uid:763623">Tony Situ</a> on <a href="/comments/1211456/50280246#c243">Mon May 27, 2013 at 04:20:10 PM PDT</a></p>
